In a message dated 2/17/03 11:29:58 AM Central Standard Time, 
airly2002@... writes:


> "Patient little one, Patient"hissed Hydras with a indulgent tone"A 
> wrong step and all would be messed up"
> 

Little one? Her optics narrowed. For a fleeting moment she thought about 
tackling him to show him that she was not as weak as she looked. But, it soon 
disappated from her mind.

"Understood." For now. She would wait... watch... plot. Then make her move. 

She didn't realize that her one 'paw' was still in his hand until she moved 
to clasp her hands behind her. The one hand stationary. Her optics went down 
to her hand in his, then her optics went up to his. Curious why they were 
still holding hands. 'Such rubblish,' she thought. But, in some other ways, 
she didn't mind. 

Then her optics went back to the map as she continued to take in the 
locations.

--part1_19b.110f5f0c.2b82f023_boundary
